Results\: Download From - List of file(s) to download in non-absolute path format Full Path to Use - Full path where downloaded files will be placed Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching. 4890e0d5-0390-406f-adf1-f6508693a73b.description=
 Description

This workflow will rollback (uninstall) a SQL Server patch on a standalone 2005/2008/2008R2 instance.  The default deployment will only show required parameters.

 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    Instance.Name - No description
    Patch Name - *Required.  The name of the patch (as seen in the Add or Remove Programs menu in Windows), the KB number of the patch, or "Latest Patch" to automatically rollback latest patch on instance.  This field is case-insensitive.
    Server.Become Routine - No description

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
    SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Download From Software Directory - No description
    Download Target Destination - No description

 Dependencies

A SQL Server 2005/2008/2008 R2 instance should already be provisioned, and previously patched at least once.
If a SQL instance has been patched multiple times, only the latest patch can be uninstalled.  Uninstalling out of sequence is not supported by Microsoft, and thus is not supported by this workflow.

 Results Verification

- In the last step, the workflow verifies that the patch no longer exists on the operating system.
- Run "SELECT @@VERSION" against the SQL Server Instance to ensure that the build level has decreased.



 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
